        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 4:26PM EDT until June 28 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 426 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Lockwood, or
near Waverly, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Barton, Waverly, Owego, Litchfield, Windham, Nichols, Lockwood, Tioga
Center, Lounsberry, and Owens Mill.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Heavy rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to flash
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
